WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
Marcel and the Shakespeare Letters by Stephen Rabley.

00:05.000 --> 00:07.000
CD-1

00:07.000 --> 00:12.000
Marcel is a French mouse.

00:12.000 --> 00:17.000
He's a detective, and he lives in Paris.

00:17.000 --> 00:22.000
But Marcel doesn't live in Paris all year.

00:22.000 --> 00:27.000
Every November, he visits London.

00:27.000 --> 00:34.000
His old friend, Henry, has a small flat there.

00:34.000 --> 00:38.000
Marcel loves London.

00:38.000 --> 00:41.000
The beautiful buildings.

00:41.000 --> 00:45.000
The big black taxis.

00:45.000 --> 00:48.000
The museums and shops.

00:48.000 --> 00:56.000
He loves Paris, but he loves London too.

00:56.000 --> 01:02.000
This story is about one of Marcel's November holidays.

01:02.000 --> 01:09.000
It starts at 3 o'clock on a Tuesday afternoon.

01:09.000 --> 01:16.000
Marcel is walking from Night's Bridge station to Henry's flat.

01:16.000 --> 01:20.000
He has two heavy bags with him.

01:20.000 --> 01:27.000
Henry's address is 42 Old Wilton Street.

01:27.000 --> 01:31.000
Marcel looks at the numbers.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
36.

01:33.000 --> 01:36.000
38.

01:36.000 --> 01:39.000
40.

01:39.000 --> 01:42.000
Yes, here it is.

01:42.000 --> 01:45.000
Number 42.

01:45.000 --> 01:48.000
He sees a sign.

01:48.000 --> 01:54.000
It says, Professor J. T. Barton.

01:54.000 --> 01:57.000
Marcel looks at it and thinks.

01:57.000 --> 02:00.000
That's new.

02:00.000 --> 02:04.000
Then he goes down to Henry's flat.

02:04.000 --> 02:08.000
Henry opens the door and smiles.

02:08.000 --> 02:15.000
Marcel, he says, come in, come in.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.000
Hello, Henry.

02:17.000 --> 02:21.000
Marcel says, how are you?

02:21.000 --> 02:24.000
His English is very good.

02:24.000 --> 02:26.000
I'm very well.

02:26.000 --> 02:28.000
And you?

02:28.000 --> 02:30.000
Yes, thanks.

02:30.000 --> 02:33.000
Good. Good.

02:33.000 --> 02:37.000
Henry takes Marcel's coat.

02:37.000 --> 02:43.000
Now, he says, let's have some tea.

02:43.000 --> 02:47.000
The two friends sit in big chairs.

02:47.000 --> 02:50.000
They drink tea and talk.

02:50.000 --> 02:58.000
At 5 o'clock, Marcel says, there's a new person in number 42.

02:58.000 --> 03:00.000
What's his name?

03:00.000 --> 03:02.000
Burton?

03:02.000 --> 03:04.000
Barnum?

03:04.000 --> 03:05.000
Barton?

03:05.000 --> 03:08.000
Henry says, Professor Barton.

03:08.000 --> 03:12.000
He's very, very clever.

03:12.000 --> 03:15.000
And that's not all.

03:15.000 --> 03:20.000
After tomorrow, he's going to be famous, too.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
Famous?

03:22.000 --> 03:25.000
Marcel looks at his English friend.

03:25.000 --> 03:27.000
Why?

03:27.000 --> 03:32.000
It's a very interesting story, Henry says.

03:32.000 --> 03:35.000
He has some letters.

03:35.000 --> 03:42.000
They were under the floor of an old woman's house in Oxford.

03:42.000 --> 03:43.000
And?

03:43.000 --> 03:45.000
Marcel says.

03:45.000 --> 03:52.000
And they're from Shakespeare to his son, Henry says.

03:52.000 --> 03:54.000
Shakespeare?

03:54.000 --> 03:56.000
Yes.

03:56.000 --> 03:58.000
Henry smiles.

03:58.000 --> 04:00.000
Shakespeare.

04:00.000 --> 04:08.000
The old lady telephoned Professor Barton and the professor visited her.

04:08.000 --> 04:11.000
They talked about the letters.

04:11.000 --> 04:19.000
And she said, I want to give them to the British Museum in London.

04:19.000 --> 04:22.000
Can you do that for me?

04:22.000 --> 04:26.000
And Professor Barton said yes.

04:26.000 --> 04:28.000
That's right.

04:28.000 --> 04:31.000
Where are the letters now?

04:31.000 --> 04:33.000
Marcel asks.

04:33.000 --> 04:41.000
In the professor's flat, he's going to give them to the British Museum tomorrow morning

04:41.000 --> 04:44.000
at ten o'clock.

04:44.000 --> 04:52.000
A lot of journalists and TV people are going to be there.

04:52.000 --> 04:55.000
Suddenly, there's a big bang.

04:55.000 --> 05:01.000
And then, along, please!

05:01.000 --> 05:03.000
What's that noise?

05:03.000 --> 05:06.000
Marcel asks.

05:06.000 --> 05:08.000
He goes to the window.

05:08.000 --> 05:11.000
Then he remembers.

05:11.000 --> 05:13.000
Oh!

05:13.000 --> 05:15.000
Fireworks!

05:15.000 --> 05:19.000
Of course, it's the fifth of November.

05:19.000 --> 05:24.000
Your Guy Fawkes day.

05:24.000 --> 05:31.000
Then, a man walks down the steps from 42 Old Wilton Street.

05:31.000 --> 05:34.000
Marcel looks at him.

05:34.000 --> 05:37.000
Is that Professor Barton?

05:37.000 --> 05:39.000
He asks.

05:39.000 --> 05:42.000
Yes, Henry answers.

05:42.000 --> 05:47.000
He always goes to the cinema on Tuesday evenings.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.000
Ah-ha!

05:49.000 --> 05:52.000
Marcel says.

05:52.000 --> 05:55.000
Why do you say, ah-ha?

05:55.000 --> 05:59.000
Henry looks at his French friend.

05:59.000 --> 06:03.000
Then suddenly, he understands.

06:03.000 --> 06:06.000
Oh!

06:06.000 --> 06:11.000
You want to look at the Shakespeare letters?

06:11.000 --> 06:13.000
He smiles.

06:13.000 --> 06:14.000
OK.

06:14.000 --> 06:18.000
Why not?

06:18.000 --> 06:24.000
After tea, the two mice visit Professor Barton's flat.

06:24.000 --> 06:28.000
There's a small hole near the front door.

06:28.000 --> 06:31.000
Henry stops in front of it.

06:31.000 --> 06:34.000
Here we are, he says.

06:34.000 --> 06:37.000
Do you want to go in first?

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
No, no.

06:39.000 --> 06:41.000
After you?

06:41.000 --> 06:44.000
Marcel says.

06:44.000 --> 06:49.000
At 5.55, they're in the professor's flat.

06:49.000 --> 06:55.000
It's very big, with a lot of old chairs and books.

06:55.000 --> 07:00.000
There are some beautiful pictures, too.

07:00.000 --> 07:04.000
Come with me, Henry says.

07:04.000 --> 07:07.000
He walks across the floor.

07:07.000 --> 07:13.000
Then, he starts to climb a very tall bookcase.

07:13.000 --> 07:16.000
Marcel is behind him.

07:16.000 --> 07:23.000
They go up and up and up for a long time.

07:23.000 --> 07:31.000
Then, Marcel sits on Charles Dickens' book, Little Dorit.

07:31.000 --> 07:35.000
He can hear a lot of fireworks in the street.

07:35.000 --> 07:37.000
Bang!

07:37.000 --> 07:38.000
Bang!

07:38.000 --> 07:39.000
Bang!

07:39.000 --> 07:40.000
Hmm.

07:40.000 --> 07:41.000
They go.

07:41.000 --> 07:42.000
Wheeee!

07:42.000 --> 07:43.000
Bow!

07:43.000 --> 07:44.000
Wush!

07:44.000 --> 07:52.000
There's a small white button in the bookcase.

07:52.000 --> 07:56.000
Henry smiles at Marcel and presses it.

07:56.000 --> 08:02.000
Suddenly, some of the books start to move.

08:02.000 --> 08:05.000
Why are they moving?

08:05.000 --> 08:07.000
Marcel says.

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
Then, he understands.

08:10.000 --> 08:15.000
Ah, I understand.

08:15.000 --> 08:18.000
There's a safe.

08:18.000 --> 08:21.000
Yes, Henry says.

08:21.000 --> 08:24.000
Now, you stay here.

08:24.000 --> 08:28.000
I'm going to open it.

08:28.000 --> 08:32.000
He takes some blue paper from his jeans.

08:32.000 --> 08:35.000
Then, he climbs down to the safe.

08:35.000 --> 08:38.000
There are some numbers on the paper.

08:38.000 --> 08:41.000
He starts to read them.

08:41.000 --> 08:43.000
55.

08:43.000 --> 08:46.000
14.

08:46.000 --> 08:49.000
62.

08:49.000 --> 08:52.000
29.

08:52.000 --> 08:54.000
8.

08:54.000 --> 08:57.000
Yes, that's right.

08:57.000 --> 09:04.000
After that, he puts his hands on the safe and moves the dial to the left.

09:04.000 --> 09:05.000
55.

09:05.000 --> 09:06.000
He says.

09:06.000 --> 09:10.000
Then, he moves the dial to the right.

09:10.000 --> 09:12.000
14.

09:12.000 --> 09:20.000
Suddenly, there's a very, very big bang!

09:20.000 --> 09:22.000
Wow!

09:22.000 --> 09:23.000
Marcel says.

09:23.000 --> 09:27.000
That was a big firework.

09:27.000 --> 09:30.000
Henry doesn't stop.

09:30.000 --> 09:33.000
62, he says.

09:33.000 --> 09:35.000
29.

09:35.000 --> 09:39.000
And, he moves the dial again.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
8.

09:41.000 --> 09:42.000
There.

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
That's it.

09:44.000 --> 09:48.000
He smiles at Marcel and opens the safe.

09:48.000 --> 09:53.000
But then suddenly, his mouth falls open.

09:53.000 --> 09:55.000
Oh, no!

09:55.000 --> 09:57.000
He says.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
What's wrong?

09:59.000 --> 10:01.000
Marcel asks.

10:01.000 --> 10:03.000
They're not here.

10:03.000 --> 10:04.000
Henry says.

10:04.000 --> 10:07.000
The Shakespeare letters.

10:07.000 --> 10:11.000
They're not here.

10:11.000 --> 10:15.000
Marcel climbs down the bookcase and looks.

10:15.000 --> 10:17.000
His friend is right.

10:17.000 --> 10:21.000
The letters aren't in the safe.

10:21.000 --> 10:23.000
But that's not all.

10:23.000 --> 10:27.000
There's a big hole at the back of the safe.

10:27.000 --> 10:30.000
And a lot of smoke, too.

10:30.000 --> 10:33.000
Marcel looks at Henry.

10:33.000 --> 10:36.000
Henry looks at Marcel.

10:36.000 --> 10:40.000
Then, they climb into the safe.

10:40.000 --> 10:42.000
Look!

10:42.000 --> 10:44.000
Marcel says.

10:44.000 --> 10:50.000
He can see a room in number 40, Old Wilton Street.

10:50.000 --> 10:53.000
He can see a person, too.

10:53.000 --> 10:57.000
A tall woman in a red dress.

10:57.000 --> 11:02.000
She's sitting at a table and talking on the telephone.

11:02.000 --> 11:06.000
Do you think Henry starts?

11:06.000 --> 11:07.000
Shh!

11:07.000 --> 11:09.000
Marcel says.

11:09.000 --> 11:13.000
The two mice sit and listen.

11:13.000 --> 11:17.000
That's right, the woman says.

11:17.000 --> 11:20.000
I'm going to New York.

11:20.000 --> 11:24.000
Yes, this evening.

11:24.000 --> 11:27.000
She writes on a notepad.

11:27.000 --> 11:29.000
Thank you!

11:29.000 --> 11:32.000
She puts down the telephone.

11:32.000 --> 11:35.000
There's a bag on the bed in front of her.

11:35.000 --> 11:40.000
In it, Marcel can see some letters.

11:40.000 --> 11:43.000
The woman closes the bag.

11:43.000 --> 11:47.000
After that, she walks to the door.

11:47.000 --> 11:53.000
She opens it and then closes it behind her.

11:54.000 --> 11:59.000
Henry looks at Marcel in the hot, dark, safe.

11:59.000 --> 12:02.000
What are we going to do?

12:02.000 --> 12:04.000
He asks.

12:04.000 --> 12:07.000
That woman's got the letters.

12:07.000 --> 12:10.000
Let's telephone the police.

12:10.000 --> 12:12.000
No.

12:12.000 --> 12:16.000
There isn't time, Marcel says.

12:16.000 --> 12:18.000
Do you know her?

12:18.000 --> 12:19.000
The woman?

12:19.000 --> 12:22.000
No, I don't.

12:22.000 --> 12:26.000
Who usually lives in that flat?

12:26.000 --> 12:28.000
Two old women.

12:28.000 --> 12:31.000
But they're on holiday in Spain.

12:31.000 --> 12:33.000
Oh, Marcel.

12:33.000 --> 12:37.000
What are we going to do?

12:37.000 --> 12:41.000
Marcel looks into the dark flat.

12:41.000 --> 12:45.000
Come with me, he says.

12:45.000 --> 12:49.000
He climbs into the old women's flat.

12:49.000 --> 12:52.000
Henry is behind him.

12:52.000 --> 12:57.000
The two mice run across the floor.

12:57.000 --> 13:01.000
Then they climb up a table.

13:01.000 --> 13:10.000
On the table there's a yellow light and a small white notepad.

13:10.000 --> 13:14.000
Marcel looks at it under the light.

13:14.000 --> 13:16.000
What are you doing?

13:16.000 --> 13:19.000
Henry asks.

13:19.000 --> 13:22.000
Marcel doesn't answer.

13:22.000 --> 13:24.000
Then he says,

13:24.000 --> 13:28.000
I was right.

13:28.000 --> 13:31.000
Can you see?

13:31.000 --> 13:33.000
Henry smiles.

13:33.000 --> 13:36.000
Yes, I can.

13:36.000 --> 13:41.000
Not very well, but it says,

13:41.000 --> 13:47.000
Concorde 720.

13:47.000 --> 13:52.000
Marcel puts down the notepad and looks at his watch.

13:52.000 --> 13:55.000
It's six o'clock.

13:55.000 --> 14:00.000
Then he starts to run down the leg of the table.

14:00.000 --> 14:04.000
Henry runs down the leg of the table too.

14:04.000 --> 14:07.000
Where are we going now?

14:07.000 --> 14:09.000
He asks.

14:09.000 --> 14:12.000
He throw airport of course.

14:12.000 --> 14:15.000
Marcel says.

14:15.000 --> 14:21.000
At 6.05, the two mice are in Old Wilton Street.

14:21.000 --> 14:24.000
It's dark and cold.

14:24.000 --> 14:29.000
They walk quickly to Knightsbridge station.

14:29.000 --> 14:32.000
There are a lot of fireworks.

14:32.000 --> 14:34.000
Bang!

14:35.000 --> 14:37.000
Boop!

14:37.000 --> 14:39.000
Whoosh!

14:39.000 --> 14:42.000
Marcel watches them.

14:42.000 --> 14:49.000
Then he remembers the very big bang in the professor's flat.

14:49.000 --> 14:53.000
That was clever, he thinks.

14:53.000 --> 14:57.000
Very, very clever.

14:57.000 --> 15:02.000
There are hundreds of people at Knightsbridge station.

15:02.000 --> 15:07.000
Marcel and Henry run under their legs and bags.

15:07.000 --> 15:11.000
Marcel can hear a noise.

15:11.000 --> 15:13.000
Quick, Henry!

15:13.000 --> 15:16.000
He says, a train's coming.

15:16.000 --> 15:18.000
He's right.

15:18.000 --> 15:22.000
A train is coming into the station.

15:22.000 --> 15:25.000
A sign on the front of it says,

15:25.000 --> 15:27.000
He throw.

15:27.000 --> 15:33.000
The doors open and the mice get on.

15:33.000 --> 15:37.000
There are fifteen stations before he throw.

15:37.000 --> 15:41.000
Every time the train stops.

15:41.000 --> 15:46.000
Henry says, quick, quick!

15:46.000 --> 15:49.000
What are we waiting for?

15:49.000 --> 15:54.000
Then the doors close and the train starts again.

15:55.000 --> 15:59.000
At Heathrow, the mice get off.

15:59.000 --> 16:03.000
Marcel looks left and right.

16:03.000 --> 16:06.000
Where do we go now?

16:06.000 --> 16:08.000
He asks.

16:08.000 --> 16:10.000
I don't know.

16:10.000 --> 16:15.000
Henry says, he looks left and right too.

16:15.000 --> 16:18.000
There are a lot of signs.

16:18.000 --> 16:22.000
Then suddenly, Henry smiles.

16:22.000 --> 16:25.000
Marcel, look!

16:25.000 --> 16:29.000
That blue sign says, Concord.

16:29.000 --> 16:32.000
Good, Marcel says.

16:32.000 --> 16:34.000
He looks at his watch.

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
It's seven-ten.

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
Let's go!

16:38.000 --> 16:43.000
He says, the mice start to run again.

16:43.000 --> 16:49.000
Marcel, Henry says, what are we going to do?

16:49.000 --> 16:53.000
Okay, we find the woman.

16:53.000 --> 16:56.000
But then what do we do?

16:56.000 --> 16:59.000
How do we get the letters back?

16:59.000 --> 17:02.000
Marcel smiles.

17:02.000 --> 17:04.000
Wait and see?

17:04.000 --> 17:06.000
He says.

17:06.000 --> 17:09.000
They come to a door.

17:09.000 --> 17:12.000
It says, Concord.

17:12.000 --> 17:14.000
But it's closed.

17:14.000 --> 17:18.000
Henry and Marcel stop in front of it.

17:18.000 --> 17:20.000
Oh no!

17:20.000 --> 17:22.000
Says Henry.

17:22.000 --> 17:28.000
But then, two men with big bags open the door and go in.

17:28.000 --> 17:31.000
The mice go in too.

17:31.000 --> 17:33.000
Good!

17:33.000 --> 17:35.000
Marcel says.

17:35.000 --> 17:38.000
He looks at the people in the room.

17:38.000 --> 17:40.000
Now!

17:40.000 --> 17:43.000
Can you see, huh?

17:43.000 --> 17:45.000
No, I can't!

17:45.000 --> 17:47.000
Henry says.

17:47.000 --> 17:49.000
Marcel smiles.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.000
I can!

17:51.000 --> 17:53.000
He says.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.000
Where?

17:55.000 --> 17:56.000
There!

17:56.000 --> 17:58.000
In front of us!

17:58.000 --> 18:00.000
Henry looks.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.000
Marcel is right.

18:02.000 --> 18:09.000
The American woman is sitting on a chair and listening to her Walkman.

18:09.000 --> 18:12.000
She's reading a newspaper too.

18:12.000 --> 18:15.000
Her bag is on the floor.

18:15.000 --> 18:16.000
Okay.

18:16.000 --> 18:18.000
Let's go!

18:18.000 --> 18:20.000
Marcel says.

18:20.000 --> 18:24.000
He takes a small knife from his coat.

18:24.000 --> 18:26.000
Walk behind me, Henry.

18:26.000 --> 18:30.000
But be very, very quiet.

18:30.000 --> 18:33.000
He starts to walk across the room.

18:33.000 --> 18:37.000
Henry walks behind his friend.

18:37.000 --> 18:40.000
Marcel's a detective.

18:40.000 --> 18:42.000
He thinks.

18:42.000 --> 18:44.000
It's going to be okay.

18:44.000 --> 18:46.000
He knows his job.

18:46.000 --> 18:49.000
He does this every day.

18:49.000 --> 18:51.000
Yes.

18:51.000 --> 18:59.000
It's going to be okay.

18:59.000 --> 19:04.000
Marcel stops in front of the American woman's bag.

19:04.000 --> 19:07.000
He looks at Henry.

19:07.000 --> 19:09.000
Shh!

19:09.000 --> 19:11.000
He says.

19:11.000 --> 19:13.000
Wait here!

19:13.000 --> 19:17.000
Then he climbs up the bag.

19:17.000 --> 19:24.000
After a short time, he starts to make a hole in it with his knife.

19:24.000 --> 19:26.000
Henry watches.

19:26.000 --> 19:29.000
His mouth is open.

19:29.000 --> 19:33.000
He looks at the American woman.

19:33.000 --> 19:37.000
She's listening to music and reading.

19:37.000 --> 19:40.000
She doesn't look down.

19:40.000 --> 19:44.000
Marcel climbs into the bag.

19:44.000 --> 19:46.000
It's dark.

19:46.000 --> 19:50.000
He closes his eyes and opens them again.

19:50.000 --> 19:54.000
Now he can see some jeans.

19:54.000 --> 19:56.000
A radio.

19:56.000 --> 19:58.000
Some books.

19:58.000 --> 20:04.000
Then suddenly he sees the Shakespeare letters.

20:04.000 --> 20:06.000
Good!

20:06.000 --> 20:08.000
He thinks.

20:08.000 --> 20:14.000
He puts the letters on his bag and starts to climb down again.

20:14.000 --> 20:18.000
Henry sees him and smiles.

20:18.000 --> 20:23.000
But then the mice hear a noise.

20:23.000 --> 20:27.000
Bing-bong!

20:27.000 --> 20:31.000
The American woman looks at her watch.

20:31.000 --> 20:39.000
Then she takes off her walkman and starts to put it in her bag.

20:39.000 --> 20:41.000
Hey!

20:41.000 --> 20:43.000
She says.

20:43.000 --> 20:44.000
What?

20:44.000 --> 20:46.000
To mice!

20:46.000 --> 20:49.000
What's this?

20:49.000 --> 20:51.000
Quick, Henry!

20:51.000 --> 20:53.000
Catch!

20:53.000 --> 20:55.000
Marcel says.

20:55.000 --> 20:58.000
He gives the letters to Henry.

20:58.000 --> 21:01.000
Then he climbs down the bag.

21:01.000 --> 21:07.000
The mice run very quickly with the Shakespeare letters.

21:07.000 --> 21:11.000
They can hear the American woman behind them.

21:11.000 --> 21:15.000
She's running very quickly too.

21:15.000 --> 21:18.000
The door is open.

21:18.000 --> 21:21.000
A man is coming in.

21:21.000 --> 21:25.000
He's fat and he has two bags.

21:25.000 --> 21:29.000
The mice run under his legs.

21:29.000 --> 21:35.000
Then Marcel hears a big noise.

21:35.000 --> 21:37.000
He looks behind him.

21:37.000 --> 21:44.000
The American woman is on the floor and the man is talking to her.

21:44.000 --> 21:46.000
Sorry?

21:46.000 --> 21:47.000
He says.

21:47.000 --> 21:50.000
Are you okay?

21:50.000 --> 21:52.000
The woman stands up.

21:52.000 --> 21:53.000
No!

21:53.000 --> 21:55.000
She says.

21:55.000 --> 22:02.000
Then she looks for the mice, but she can't see them.

22:02.000 --> 22:12.000
At nine o'clock, Marcel and Henry are back at Professor Barton's flat in Old Wilton Street.

22:12.000 --> 22:15.000
They're very happy.

22:15.000 --> 22:19.000
Marcel is sitting on the table.

22:19.000 --> 22:23.000
The Shakespeare letters are in front of him.

22:23.000 --> 22:26.000
He's reading them.

22:26.000 --> 22:30.000
Henry is standing at the window.

22:30.000 --> 22:34.000
He's watching the fireworks.

22:34.000 --> 22:38.000
Suddenly, he sees a man in a brown coat.

22:38.000 --> 22:41.000
It's Professor Barton.

22:41.000 --> 22:43.000
He's coming home.

22:43.000 --> 22:46.000
The professor is smiling.

22:46.000 --> 22:52.000
Then he walks into his flat and suddenly he stops smiling.

22:52.000 --> 22:57.000
Marcel and Henry are standing behind a chair.

22:57.000 --> 23:00.000
They watch him.

23:00.000 --> 23:02.000
He goes to the safe.

23:02.000 --> 23:04.000
It's open.

23:04.000 --> 23:07.000
He looks in it and says,

23:07.000 --> 23:11.000
Oh no!

23:11.000 --> 23:16.000
Then he sees the Shakespeare letters on the table.

23:16.000 --> 23:21.000
But he puts one hand on his head.

23:21.000 --> 23:24.000
I don't understand.

23:24.000 --> 23:27.000
He looks at the safe.

23:27.000 --> 23:30.000
Then he looks at the letters.

23:30.000 --> 23:35.000
And then he looks at the safe again.

23:35.000 --> 23:38.000
Why are the letters here?

23:38.000 --> 23:41.000
He says, When?

23:41.000 --> 23:43.000
How?

23:43.000 --> 23:47.000
I don't understand.

23:47.000 --> 23:54.000
In the morning, Henry and Marcel go to the British Museum.

23:54.000 --> 23:58.000
It's a cold day and it's raining.

23:58.000 --> 24:04.000
In the museum, there are a lot of journalists and TV people.

24:04.000 --> 24:08.000
They're waiting for Professor Barton.

24:08.000 --> 24:12.000
He arrives at ten o'clock.

24:12.000 --> 24:14.000
Good morning!

24:14.000 --> 24:17.000
He says to them.

24:17.000 --> 24:21.000
He starts to talk about the Shakespeare letters.

24:21.000 --> 24:27.000
Then he gives the letters to a man from the museum.

24:27.000 --> 24:30.000
Thank you very much, Professor.

24:31.000 --> 24:36.000
Henry and Marcel are standing at the back of the room.

24:36.000 --> 24:40.000
Henry smiles at his French friend.

24:40.000 --> 24:45.000
And thank you, Marcel, he says.

